  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed via comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling across all model inputs, propagating variability in fluid viscosity, rotational speed, inlet flow rate, and geometric tolerances through the hemolysis power-law model. The UQ results confirm that predicted RH values remain below 1.0 across the full input distribution at all five operating points.",
